Im still a bit pissed about today-my first day of ISS this year (regardless of shit I have said). I was doing good. Here is why I went there...in gym class, we have to change. If we dont-we sit out its that simple. However, we have a male coach. I guess he favors the girls, because, it dosent matter if THEY dont change. So, I got a group of the boys to rebel against the system (hooray for anarchy!) and not change until the girls were punished for it. I guess the dumb shit didnt get the point...because he asked ME (only me...out of 6 of us) WHY I DIDNT CHANGE? He said "Do you think you are better than the rest of us?" I simply replyed "No, but apparently you think the girls are way better than me, as you would NEVER say anything to THEM". He said "that is a dirty lie the girls get the same exact treatment as the boys do!".I had had it so, as I lost it I yelled "Fuck you! You wouldnt know your ass from your dick"...and he made me go to ISS...rather-I walked out because I was about to get an assult charge. My favorite teacher Mrs.Culkin came to my rescue and questioned why I was there, I told my story to her and she said I should go talk to coach at the end of the period...well I did.I told him that the girls always got to play, even if they didnt change. He gave me some bullshit about how if they dont change for 3 times a semester, he sends them to ISS, everytime. I told him that he could bullshit me and call me crazy until he was blue in the face, but the other boys and I know whats going on, and we are not as stupid as we look. At that point I walked out again, as I was going to bust him in the face. The bastard with his authority...on a liter note...Im out. Im going swimming! Third time this season. I love swimming.
